// The kernel's own structural types (§11.2 / §12.6), made first-class: Tree, Frame,
// NeutralMeta, Action, RespondShape, MetaShape. Pins (a) that they are types and
// real kernel values inhabit them, (b) the kernel self-typing its metadata via
// auto-verify (make_meta : Tree -> Tree -> MetaShape ; inert_respond : RespondShape),
// and (c) the Rung-3 wall: an INSPECTING respond does not inhabit RespondShape.
open use "../prelude.disp"
open use "../kernel/prelude.disp"

// ---- the structural types are types ----
test typecheck Type Tree        = Ok TT
test typecheck Type Frame       = Ok TT
test typecheck Type NeutralMeta = Ok TT
test typecheck Type Action      = Ok TT
test typecheck Type RespondShape = Ok TT
test typecheck Type MetaShape   = Ok TT

// ---- InvalidType is a REAL empty type now (§12.6 / STRICTTYPE.md step 1) ----
// Promoted from the old `FF` sentinel to a make_recognizer wait-form with a MetaShape
// meta, so `type_meta InvalidType` is a real record (no more `.respond` off `FF`).
test typecheck Type InvalidType    = Ok TT  // it is a Type
test tree_eq InvalidType False     = FF      // kept DISTINCT from the empty proposition
test param_apply InvalidType zero  = Ok FF   // nothing inhabits it (recognizer is Ok FF)

// ---- real kernel values inhabit them ----
test param_apply Tree zero                                       = Ok TT // Tree is permissive (any tree)
test param_apply NeutralMeta { stored_type := Nat; payload := zero } = Ok TT
test param_apply Action (Extend Nat)                             = Ok TT
test param_apply Action (Reduce zero)                            = Ok TT
test param_apply Action (Return zero)                            = Ok TT // alias: Reduce (Ok zero)
test tree_eq (Return zero) (Reduce (Ok zero))                    = TT    // Return IS the alias, definitionally
// a real neutral's meta is a NeutralMeta
test typecheck NeutralMeta (type_meta (make_hyp Nat 0))          = Ok TT

// ---- the kernel's metadata records inhabit MetaShape ----
test typecheck MetaShape (make_meta unit_witness inert_respond)  = Ok TT
test typecheck MetaShape (type_meta Bool)                        = Ok TT // a live type's actual metadata
test typecheck MetaShape (type_meta (Pi Nat ({_} -> Bool)))      = Ok TT
test param_apply MetaShape zero                                  = Ok FF // a non-record is not a MetaShape

// RespondShape is defined `Tree -> Tree -> Frame -> Action` (the `->` sugar), in a
// raw-loaded kernel fragment. This pins that a `: Type := <arrow>` alias compiles to
// the SAME Pi tree as the function-application `Arrow` form (the raw-load type-mode
// fix) — i.e. `->` is mode-independent for type aliases.
test tree_eq RespondShape (Arrow Tree (Arrow Tree (Arrow Frame Action))) = TT

// ---- RespondShape (post §12.6 Part-A re-contract): respond = {params, self, frame} -> Action ----
// hyp_reduce now extracts the metadata once and passes params + reconstructed self, so
// responds no longer raw-read `type_meta` of an abstract stored type. But that alone
// does NOT make the inspecting responds typeable:
// - inert_respond ignores all three args -> parametric -> inhabits RespondShape.
test param_apply RespondShape inert_respond = Ok TT
// - inductive/eq/telescope PROJECT off `frame` (`frame.motive`, `pair_fst frame`). Under
//   RespondShape, `frame : Tree` is abstract, so `frame.motive` routes to Tree's inert
//   respond -> InvalidType, and applying that to the self-neutral trips the walker -> Err.
//   Fixing this needs a per-former STRUCTURED Frame type (Part C), so `frame.motive` is a
//   real motive. (When that lands, these flip to Ok TT.) The single-use responds are
//   inlined into their formers now, so read them off the live metas.
// (these do NOT inhabit RespondShape — checked robustly as ≠ Ok TT, since the
// single-walk `at` makes the rejection a stuck non-verdict rather than a clean Err).
test tree_eq (param_apply RespondShape inductive_respond) (Ok TT) = FF
test tree_eq (param_apply RespondShape ((type_meta (Eq Nat zero zero)).respond)) (Ok TT) = FF
test tree_eq (param_apply RespondShape ((type_meta (Telescope t)).respond)) (Ok TT) = FF
// ...but with the frame STRUCTURED (InductiveFrame), the projecting inductive respond DOES
// inhabit its per-former shape — the §7 wall, validated in-tree (the merged apply_policed
// carve-out makes `frame.motive self` type-check). This is the StrictType-wiring milestone.
test param_apply InductiveRespondShape inductive_respond = Ok TT
// And the StrictType-realistic check: pin params to each type's OWN recognizer_params, then
// the PLAIN projecting family inhabits the one ProjectingRespondShape — plain inductive
// (Unit/Ord, params ignored) and Eq's J-rule (reads `params.rhs`, fine once pinned).
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((type_meta Unit).respond (type_meta Unit).recognizer_params) = Ok TT
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((type_meta Ord).respond (type_meta Ord).recognizer_params)   = Ok TT
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((type_meta (Eq Nat zero zero)).respond (type_meta (Eq Nat zero zero)).recognizer_params) = Ok TT
// RESIDUAL — recursive gated Nat: the coherence GATE itself is the wall, not the frame. Even fed
// cleanly-typed neutral fields built directly (motive/base/step), the respond doesn't reduce to a
// typeable Action — the recursive check `step : Π n. motive n -> motive (succ n)` (mint n + ih,
// check the dependent application under nested bind_hyp) doesn't self-type under abstract cases.
// Non-recursive gated (Bool) DOES inhabit; so the open frontier is the recursive inductive ELIMINATOR.
test tree_eq (param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((type_meta Nat).respond (type_meta Nat).recognizer_params)) (Ok TT) = FF

// NEGATIVE former (Pi): its `at FF` respond, params PINNED to the spine `[mint A ; apply (B h)]`,
// inhabits `Self -> A -> Action` — the elimination frame IS the argument (: the domain A), and the
// walk lands `Extend (B arg)`. So for `Pi Nat ({_} -> Bool)` the per-former shape is
// `Tree -> Nat -> Action`. This is §7B self-typing the spine, validated in-tree for the Pi face.
test param_apply (Arrow Tree (Arrow Nat Action)) ((type_meta (Pi Nat ({_} -> Bool))).respond (type_meta (Pi Nat ({_} -> Bool))).recognizer_params) = Ok TT
// NEGATIVE formers Sigma/Record (PROJECTION-lead): params PINNED, frame : Frame (Tree). Unlike Pi
// (which APPLIES its codomain to the frame, so frame : A), a projection respond only READS
// `pair_fst frame` and threads `source (acc name)` — no application — so the frame stays abstract
// Tree and the field-name branch doesn't block. Shape `Self -> Frame -> Action`.
test param_apply (Arrow Tree (Arrow Frame Action)) ((type_meta (Sigma Nat ({_} -> Bool))).respond (type_meta (Sigma Nat ({_} -> Bool))).recognizer_params) = Ok TT
test param_apply (Arrow Tree (Arrow Frame Action)) ((type_meta (Record (cons (pair "a" Nat) t))).respond (type_meta (Record (cons (pair "a" Nat) t))).recognizer_params) = Ok TT
// - Pi's / Nat's responds now TERMINATE (STRICTTYPE.md step 1): with InvalidType a
//   real empty type, eliminating an InvalidType-neutral runs a well-defined inert
//   respond instead of projecting `.respond` out of `FF` and looping. They still do
//   NOT inhabit RespondShape (the Part-C reason: `params`/`frame` are unstructured
//   Tree, so projecting off them under abstract inputs is ill-formed) — a stuck
//   non-verdict (≠ Ok TT) under the single-walk `at`.
test tree_eq (param_apply RespondShape ((type_meta Nat).respond)) (Ok TT) = FF
test tree_eq (param_apply RespondShape ((type_meta (Pi Nat ({_} -> Bool))).respond)) (Ok TT) = FF
